examples.content:
Peel 2 cloves of garlic and mince garlic. Combine 1/6 cup water, 1/8 cup soy sauce, 1 tablespoon honey, 2 cloves minced garlic, 1/2 tablespoon minced fresh ginger, 1/8 teaspoon black pepper, 1 teaspoon cornstarch in a small bowl. Whisk to mix. Set aside. Take 8 in number broccoli florets. Take 3 cremini mushrooms, and slice them. Take 1 bell pepper and slice 1/2 of the bell pepper. Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the broccoli and sliced mushrooms and cook, stirring often, for 4 minutes. If the pan gets too hot on medium-high, turn the heat down to medium. Add the bell pepper and continue cooking, stirring often, for 2-3 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender. Whisk the sauce again to recombine the ingredients. Pour the sauce into the pan and cook, stirring, for 1 minute until the sauce thickens.
